{"id": 5249, "title": "Ticket #5249: OOM killer score adjustment isn't low enough", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe starter lowers the /proc/pid/oom_adj or /proc/pid/oom_score_adj for jobs, so that the OOM killer is biased to be more likely to chose a job instead of a condor daemon or other user process on the machine.  Unfortunately, chrome also does this for its tabs, and at a larger level than condor.  For systems with /proc/pid/oom_score_adj, set the value to 800 instead of 16, so that condor jobs will be chosen over chrome tabs, which are at 300.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Sep-09 22:20:03 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW:</strong> Looks good</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Sep-09 22:03</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=45806\">[45806]</a></span>: Version history for <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=5249\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5249'); return false;\" title=\"OOM killer score adjustment isn't low enough\">#5249</a></span>  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Sep-09 21:55</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=45805\">[45805]</a></span>: Set OOM killer score more aggresively <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=5249\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5249'); return false;\" title=\"OOM killer score adjustment isn't low enough\">#5249</a></span> Committer: Tim Theisen  (By Greg Thain )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" val